<item>
            <title>[HBASE-850] bin/hbase should check `which java` to find java</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-850</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the bin/hbase script tries to find java in JAVA_HOME/bin/java. If JAVA_HOME isn&apos;t set, it errors out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, I think it should check `which java 2&amp;gt;/dev/null` to see if there is a java on the user&apos;s PATH. If a java is on the user&apos;s path, the script should just set JAVA=java.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
