                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12629587" author="irubin" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2008 19:59:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we&apos;re going to pass on this one.  the bin/hbase script first calls conf/hbase-env.sh, which should define JAVA_HOME.  JAVA_HOME really should be defined in conf/hbase-env.sh... it&apos;s one of the few strictly required configurations, so if it isn&apos;t defined there&apos;s a much bigger problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12715302" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 1 Jun 2009 23:32:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;we need to be really careful here - on most Debian based distros, the standard /usr/bin/java is a highly obsolete, non-sun JDK that is 150% inappropriate for running HBase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Falling back on a non-sun JVM is never going to be the right thing to do for a while. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12715577" author="bien" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2009 16:39:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; we need to be really careful here - on most Debian based distros, the standard /usr/bin/java is a highly obsolete, non-sun JDK that is 150% inappropriate for running HBase. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That sounds like a different problem.  I have machines where /usr/bin/java is the correct Sun java to use.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12795660" author="stack" created="Thu, 31 Dec 2009 20:06:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Addressed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2074&quot; title=&quot;Improvements to the hadoop-config script&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2074&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2074&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
